Isicebit. “ Although.'' In the sense of licet or quamvis.—60. Repotia. The repotia was an entertainment given by the husband on the day after the marriage, when presente were sent to the bride by her friends and relations, and she began to act as mistress of the family by performing sacred rites.--Dierum festos. A Graecism for dies festos—61. Albatus. “ Clothed in white.'' The general colour of the Roman toga was white; this colom, however, was peculiarly adopted bv the guests, or those who bore a part at formal banquets, or on occasions of ceremony.—Ipse. “ With his own hands.” In this showing his mean and sordid habits, since, afraid that his guests, or his slaves, should be too profuse of his oil, bad as it was, he pours it out himself.
